verbose_text: There were two noticeable differences : (1) the relative weight of signals across the Ex1 tip region, surrounding the double cysteine motif, varied between the LBD and NTD and (2) within Ex1, LBD binding to the N-terminal end of the loop was greater, whereas interaction with the tip region of the loop was reduced (XREF_FIG C).
evidence: LBD binding to the N-terminal end
